 Joseph Erunke – Abuja THE Nigerian Army on Saturday elevated 40 senior officers from the rank of Brigadier General to Major General in a major promotion exercise in the force. The army also promoted about 120 other senior officers to the rank of Brigadier General. A statement issued by the acting Director of Army Public Relations, Col. Sagir Musa, said the promotion followed earlier approval to that effect by the Nigerian Army Council. Continue reading Army promotes 40 Brigadier Generals, 120 others at Vanguard News. Source: Vanguard Also 92 Colonels to rank of Brigadier Generals By Joseph Erunke ABUJA-THE Nigerian Army Council has promoted 45 senior officers from the rank of Brigadier Generals to that of Major Generals. President Buhari interacts with troops of HQ 1 BDE in Dansadau Zamfara State as part of the 2016 Nigerian… November 20, 2017 In "News" The Nigerian Army Council on Monday approved the promotion of 45 Brigadier Generals to the rank of Major Generals and 92 Colonels to the rank of Brigadier Generals. The announcement was made in a statement by Brigadier General Sani Kukasheka Usman, Director Army Public Relations. Some of those promoted to… November 20, 2017 In "News" BY FRANCIS OKOYE, Maiduguri The Nigerian Army Council has yesterday approved the promotion of 45 Brigadier Generals to the rank of Major Generals and 92 Colonels to the rank of Brigadier Generals. According to statement issued to newsmen in Maiduguri by the director Army Public Relations, Brig Gen Sani Kukashekau… November 21, 2017 In "News"